body_html: I think the problem here is that you have a file called tensorflow.py in your current directory. Python will interpret import tensorflow as tf as an instruction to load that script, rather than the installed TensorFlow module. Renaming that file to something else should fix the problem.

body: I think the problem here is that you have a file called `tensorflow.py` in your current directory. Python will interpret `import tensorflow as tf` as an instruction to load that script, rather than the installed TensorFlow module. Renaming that file to something else should fix the problem.
